DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,5);
$b = random(1,9);
$c = random(1,9);
$b2=$b*$b;
$a2=$a*$a;

$ans1 = $b**2-($a**2)/3;
$ans2 = 0;
$ans3 = (8/15)*($a**5);
BEGIN_TEXT

Notice that the curve given by the parametric equations
\[ x=$b2 - t^2      \]
\[    y= t^3 - $a2 t     \]
is symetric about the x-axis.  (If t gives us the point (x,y), then -t will give
(x,-y) ).  
$BR
$BR
At which x value is the tangent to this curve horizontal?
$BR
At x =  \{ ans_rule(10) \}
END_TEXT
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
At which t value is the tangent to this curve vertical?
$BR
At t =  \{ ans_rule(10) \}
END_TEXT
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR The curve makes a loop which lies along the x-axis.  What is
the total area inside the loop?
$BR
Area =  \{ ans_rule(40) \}
END_TEXT
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));

